paragraph.content:
EXAMINATION: MRI BRAIN & STEM W/WO CONT: 2020-02-14 11:00 AM, MR190537238
CLINICAL HISTORY: Meningioma status post brain surgery
COMPARISON: None
FINDINGS: Multiple pulse sequences and multiple imaging planes were acquired in the evaluation of the brain before and after the intravenous administration of 20 mL MultiHance contrast.
Postoperative changes are demonstrated anteriorly, right of midline. Encephalomalacia is demonstrated involving the right frontal region. After the intravenous administration of contrast, there is no abnormal parenchymal or meningeal enhancement about the operative site to suggest residual and/or recurrent tumor. However, a tiny round focus of enhancement is demonstrated adjacent to the left temporal lobe posteriorly best visualized on series 13 image 10 and series 12 image 7 measuring 6 mm x 9 mm.
Punctate and confluent FLAIR signal abnormality is demonstrated involving the subcortical and periventricular deep white matter bilaterally likely related to sequela from small vessel vasculopathy and clinical correlation is advised.
There is no evidence of diffusion restriction to suggest recent infarction. There is no evidence of intraparenchymal hemorrhage. The craniocervical junction is unremarkable. The upper cervical spinal cord is normal in appearance. The ventricles are normal in size and symmetry. There are no intra-axial masses identified. Vascular flow voids are unremarkable.
IMPRESSION:
1. Postoperative changes are demonstrated anteriorly, right of midline. There is no evidence to suggest residual or recurrent enhancing tumor about the operative site.
2. Tiny enhancing extra-axial focus adjacent to the left temporal lobe measuring 6 mm x 9 mm, likely a small meningioma. Continued short-term follow-up is recommended to document stability.
